description: After completing titles like the critically acclaimed The Horror Show and Nightmare Unknown, Maddox has continued his comic career with stories like THE DEAD (illustrated by Jen Hickman), CLOWN (illustrated by Brandon Lauhon),and the wildly anticipated BLUE NEMESIS (illustrated by Steve Scott). A versatile and prolific writer/creator, Maddox's has only just begun to find and impress his audience.
name: James Maddox

deck: Ex-glamour model turned comic book writer and creator.
name: Jocelyn Potter

description:
Nick "OG" O'Gorman is a Canadian artist who has worked in all areas of the medium: pencilling, lettering, inking, colouring and writing.

Based in the nation's capital, Ottawa, Nick has been working in the industry for 3 years and considers the time spent working an absolute pleasure.

Aside from drawing, Nick spends his time reading, playing guitar and singing in the hardrock/post-hardcore band Sweet Alps.
name: Nick O'Gorman

description: Eugen (or Eugene) is an artist from Republic of Moldova, in Europe. Before becoming a colorist he was an artist and inker, but wasn't satisfied with it so he changed his path and started to color.
name: Eugen Beţivu

description: Luca Cicchitti is a comic book artist from Italy.
name: Luca Cicchitti

description: Brandon Rhiness is a comic book writer and creator from Edmonton, Alberta, Canada. He co-created the Higher Universe comic book company with Adam Storoschuk. Brandon is the creator and writer of Stargirl and the co-creator of Misfits and Ghoul Squad.
name: Brandon Rhiness

description: Adam Storoschuk is a comic book artist and creator. He is from Vegreville, Alberta, Canada but currently works and lives in Edmonton. Adam co-created the Higher Universe comic book company with Brandon Rhiness. He is the original creator of Misfits and Ghoul Squad.
name: Adam Storoschuk

description: Pitbull-X is a SUPERHERO mature audience digital comic book. Based on a alternate universe on the planet HTRAE, 3 super-soldiers, PITBULL-X, EVE-X and DAETH_X, must question their choices and face that to truly save the innocents of their world, they must take out the real culprits of terror on the masses. Time grow short as the inner circle through lies deceits and the media are about to create a ONE WORLD ORDER UNDER A CENTRAL BANK SYSTEM, where the masses will be slaves to the the corporate, agenda of the ELITE 1%.
name: Eric Valric

description: Nuno Teixeira (nickname "XEI", pronounced "shay") works within the corporate world by day, and works within fictional worlds by night.
name: Nuno XEI

description:
A Detroit native born and raised, Chris chased his dreams to Tinseltown in 2001. In the decade since, he has built an extensive resume as an Art Director and Motion Graphics Artist for some of Hollywood's top companies, while still maintaining his own creative endeavors, writing and directing multiple independent projects.

Chris currently lives in the suburbs of Los Angeles with his wife and their adopted mutt, Harley.
name: Chris Callahan

deck: Writer and artist; created Snow. Also the video game developer behind indie horror game Home.
name: Benjamin Rivers

deck: Patrick "Doodles" Handlon is a writer and artist from Indianapolis, Indiana. He began his career writing and drawing for a 'zine called "Aunt Ida" in the mid nineties (at times under the pen name Pol Pat). After the demise of "Aunt Ida" he wrote and drew the mini comics "Little Doodles" and "The Beat Generation". From the late nineties until 2013 Doodles released no new comics. In 2013 a new series "Wastes of Space" debuted followed quickly by "FruitBat" and a new incarnation of "Little Doodles".
name: Doodles Handlon

description:
During the first 30 years of the 20 century the most popular writer of mystery/thrillers was Edgar Wallace, it being said that during the 30’s one out of every four books sold in England was written by Edgar Wallace. He died in 1932 on his way to Hollywood to take part in the scripting of the film "King Kong. "(In the end, while given credit because it was thought his name would help sell tickets, he really contributed nothing to it.).

After that, his fame in England, Canada, and the States started to fade, so he is seldom reprinted and almost forgotten, however he remains popular in Germany were his novels remain a favorite.

He was still popular enough in 1951 to warrant a comic book in Australia that did adaptations of his stories.
name: Edgar Wallace
